{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Their review concentrated on distinct GANs by identifying their common characteristics based on this working resource.Handalage et al. [18] reviewed \"Deep Convolutional GAN (DCGAN), Laplacian GAN (LapGAN), Wasserstein GAN (WGAN), Information Maximizing GAN (InfoGAN), Conditional GAN (CGAN), Energy-based GAN (EBGAN), Boundary Equilibrium GAN (BEGAN), Progressive Growing GAN (PGGAN), Big GAN (BigGAN), and Style-based Generative Architecture\" for GANs.",
    "Additionally, their fundamental developmental mechanism and goal-oriented functions were investigated.",
    "Second, the most popular GAN variations were presented, along with their advantages and disadvantages.",
    "Thirdly, a few of the industries and uses where GANs have been successful were examined.",
    "In this study, they created a GAN model and assessed the advantages and disadvantages of it."
  ],
